value:
I detest mortals... If not for them,
I would still be at my brother's side.

When I was young, I was tormented
for the way I looked. Only my brother
was ever kind to me...$k$pOnly he showed me love.

It was you who summoned me, then.
I will do as you wish...

You alone deserve my respect.
Give me your orders—but I won't
tolerate being spoken down to.

You've interrupted my reminiscence.
What is it that you want?

I am Freyja, lest you forget. To you
lowly mortals, I am nothing less than
a god.
A queen's power.

Serving under mortals...
Humiliation yet again.

Could it be that I have not fully
adapted to life outside the dream?

If you insist. But how will this
change me?

I am Freyja, ruler of Dökkálfheimr,
a god from beyond this mortal realm.
To be summoned here... Disgraceful.

Dream or reality? You chose reality.
And you reunited with your friends.$k$pReality shifts with time, though,
doesn't it? To rejoin reality is not
an ending, nor is it happy.$k$pReality is cruel... Being from that cold
world of steel, you should know such
truths well, $Nu.$k$pIf you wish, I could offer you a dream.
A little escape...$k$pYou could be free from the anxieties
of the future... No sadness or pain...
You could be free from it all, forever.$k$pSo, I ask again: Dream or reality?
Which do you choose?
やっ！
それっ
きゃああっ！
Rude...
So unpleasant!
A dream neverending.
You'll see...
A cruel dream, then!
Oh, Freyr...
Laugh
I am Freyja... To mortals, I am known as the goddess of love.
Ah! Unforgivable! You're not Freyr.
The love my brother and I feel is deeper than most siblings...
Since the day Freyr rebuffed me, I have made the realm of nightmares my home.
I am so much more than any lowly mortal. I demand your respect.
Why, Freyr? My love for you... Why?
You resemble him not one iota. So tell me...why do I care?
Yes.
Just you try.
Expect nothing less.
